data.description: Must see 3 bedroom, 2 bathroom home in the highly desired Shenandoah Estates subdivision. This home opens to a spacious living room with a gorgeous wood burning/gas fireplace that seamlessly transitions into the dining room and kitchen. The kitchen is equipped with an abundance of cabinet space. Lots of room for family and friends with a large den equipped with a wet bar or coffee station. The back yard offers a spacious open patio that has ample amount of room for full set of outdoor furniture. The open patio overlooks the massive fenced-in green space with mature trees. You'll love this central location in Baton Rouge- walking distance to the elementary school, close to restaurants, shopping, and more! Luxury vinyl plank flooring throughout, freshly landscaped, roof is 4 years old, AC is less than 1 year old, attic has been sealed  Don't miss the opportunity to own this remarkable home.  Contact us today to schedule a private showing.
